reviews: The room was perfect for us. All the things we needed and the space was well used. The view from the room on the top was nice. Good safety with a looked gate to the street. Staff was very friendly. In no time we could be at the Metrostation, from where it was easy to change for the airport, the city and Disney. Fine baker and cafees nearby.

The concerts got moved to November 2022, but even that I offered to pay EXTRA and so on, the hotel wouldent rebook to the new dates, even that september was sold out and november was free. So we had to go anyway, in order not to lose money on this. The staff was friendly, only good thing to say about this place. I cannot recormend anyone to go there. Nothing I read holds up. The room was cold, theres a draft from doors, the beds are like bricks and the floor is so cold. The beding is a blanket and a sheet, and since there was NO heat, we had to sleep with clothes on and socks. Even the towelwarmer in bathroom dident work, so all was cold and wet, after a bath. First night to hob dident work, and man in reception dident know how to turn it on, so we had to eat out. 45 Euro for 2 pizzas and water. The supermarket barely had anything (Aldi and LIDL), Lidl is a bit from the hotel. And the territory arround is dreadfull. We dident feel safe at all. Middeleast people everywhere, smoking weed and yelling stuff at us (proberly because my daugther held my hand) and beggers at the subway. All shops was kinda closed and grafitti and trash everywhere. I never feelt so scared anywhere. Many times the police held up people to tjek them (proberly for drugs). I wouldent ever go back there or recormend anyone going there.

Great location within easy walk to M3 Rue Saint-Maur station. Comfortable neighborhood. Unusual two-level building with secured entrance to central courtyard. My studio was the smallest I've ever stayed in, but it had all the essentials for a self-catered stay. Clean. Quiet. Helpful staff. Excellent value for Paris. Will ask for upper level unit next time for greater privacy.

Quiet accommodation. A mini apartment with kitchenette, on two floors, simple and well finished, with a French touch. The neighborhood gives an immediate feeling of well-being: typical grocery stores, small restaurants, two metro stops (M2 and M3) nearby.

The hotel is easy to reach from Gard de Nord train station being only 6 stops on Metro Line 2 and then a 5 minute walk. However its half way down a small road which is easy to miss in the dark so pay attention.

The rooms are based either side of a central passageway and on either the ground or first floor, accessed by stairs, no lifts. I was on the first floor and this was not a problem for me but might be for others. I had a Standard Double Studio which has the bedroom partially separate from the small kitchenette and shower room / toilet. The room was quiet and, although small, normal for Paris.

Everything was provided as expected including a nice coffee machine but only 1 coffee capsule and 2 tea bags, as I was there for 4 nights I bought more from the local supermarket. The room was quiet during my stay and neither too hot nor cold. The only negative point I would make is although this was a 'Double' the bed was pushed up against the wall meaning that a second person would have to get out of bed by climbing over the other person or via the end of the bed, fortunately I was on my own but maybe a question to ask booking.

Overall the hotel and room met by expectations and I would stay there again,

We very much enjoyed staying at the hotel. It's got a quirky layout with the kitchen/living area downstairs and the sleeping area/bathroom upstairs. I can recommend but not in the weekend we were there: the heatwave meant we didn't sleep at all. The area itself is eclectic. Don't let that be a reason not to visit. I never felt uneasy and we also managed to score excellent Maroccan food for a stupidly cheap price.

Highlight: very well maintained and clean.
Low point: heatwave without air conditioning (fans were available but were next to useless).

A Small room with the basic amenities, Great neighborhood, food, shopping and access to public transportation are within a 15 minute walk. We chose to pick up fresh croissants from the bakery at the end of the street every morning, along with groceries from the stores in the area. Easy on the budget, in a Non-tourist area!

Very clean hotel. Option of smoking rooms. All basic amenities like microwave, electric kettle, utensils, crockery, cutlery, refrigerator, stove etc provided. A couple of minutes walk to metro and a variety of restaurants and shops.

modern, tastefully decorated apartments, light and bright, on arrival can upgrade if available as units are different, we were shown 4 different ones and decided on smaller bathroom for bigger kitchen.
Clean and well maintained
Deserves more than 2 stars

Clean, comfortable, well appointed rooms. Quiet and safe accomodation. Great service from the staff. Great location in Paris. Set in old stables/fire station, multiple choice of rooms, each one of which is unique: range from small/a bit poky, to good intermediate, to excellent / large but more expensive. Hotel desk is very helpful and pleasant.
Bathrooms good but small, good kitchenette.

This hotel (shouldn't classified as hotel) is extremely overpriced and is not worthy of the money. It has no service at all. No reception after 11pm. No phone in room for guest to contact staff. No emergency contact no. No rubbish bin in toilet. No clearing of rubbish during my 3-night stay , not unless you pay extra. I had to clear the rubbish while staying in a "hotel" on holiday. Coffee only on arrival and no refill. Microwave rack wobbles. Shower area is the smallest I've ever seen.

The first night when we came back after a long day, we found out that there was only a thin, old blanket on the bed in the cold weather of Paris which was -1C. I went to the reception but nobody there. I tried to look through my emails and internet to find the number, hoping to get extra blanket. I used my own mobile phone to call. Finally somebody picked up the phone but said the blanket should be enough and kept telling me that I should have called before 11, before reception closed. He did give us extra blankets, but in a very grumpy way. And there was no hairdryer in room. When I couldn't find the hairdryer after showering, I used my own mobile phone to call reception. Guess what? He told me to go downstairs to get the hairdryer! (Which means I need to go downstairs, walk outside the building, in the subzero degree Celsius with wet hair). I requested him to sent it to our room in a very polite way. He sighed, then silenced, and reluctantly said yes.

And there was smell of piss as lots of piss stain on the pavement just outside the hotel.

Stayed here in August. It was HOT! no A/C - at night the temperature cooled down enough to get good sleep. I guess I am spoiled with A/C. Close walk to the Metro - very important in Paris. Stay near the Metro. The rooms are clean and neat but very small. Comes with refrigerator and kitchen. Close walk to restaurants, metro, supermarket, pharmacy and more. The front desk staff and housekeeping are very nice people. Super attentive. I would definitely stay here again.

There was little inventory left in the Paris market, but we caught this one and were glad for it. Nothing fancy, but well equipped on the inside and well located on the outside. In particular we appreciated the Portuguese lady at the front desk for her sunny disposition and helpfulness.

The hotel is in a really quiet neighbourhood. The employees are really friendly and nice, they gave us a lot of information!
The hotel is clean and quiet as well. They bring breakfast to bed, which made everything even more fascinating!
The hotel is close to Menilmontant's metro station.

Have visited the hotel in September.The staff was extremely helpful.Izabel and she,s coworker (sorry,don,t know shes name)did their best when I come and during my stay.
The location is very convenient close to the metro and all food amenities.Didn,t wait any minute for check-in.The room was ready and I like it.Especially,kitchenette.Yes,washroom is small,but,remember,
it,s Paris.Hotel is clean and pretty modern for that price range.Can,t complain about internet.Wi-Fi on my phone was pretty fast.Did all I need on line.You can come to the hotel anytime,you carry the key with you.Thank you,again for your hospitality!If I have a chance to visit Paris,will choose L,Horloge again.Warm greetings to Izabel and your associate from Vlad. Canada,Ontario.

I believe it is the worst hotel I have ever visited. I have booked the stay at this terrible hostel for 4 days, and I have terminated my booking the very next day! Not only they lie on Booking.com site, by promising fast Wifi access from rooms, pleasant rooms, and nice showers. All of them was lie! The internet was very slow, and even so, you would not be able to use this from your room, cause there is no coverage. The shower rooms were shared and disgusting! I could not even close the door of the shared shower room!!!

If you want to enjoy your stay in Paris, DO NOT VISIT THIS HOTEL!

I cant start to explain.. so i will just say that the washrooms where not in a condition that you will like to step in.. :(
Plz do something about the cleanliness and smell I couldnt step in there. I was the worst.

I was staying here for 4 days, but has to check out the next day itself. there was loud noise form the next door room/apartment. couldn't seep the whole night. The owners also couldn't do anything about it.

The hotel is under renovation. We stayed a room just renovated with new furnishings/kitchenware/bedding, etc. The staff were very helpful and nice. good location to access Metro. The hotel is about 30-45 min away from CDG airport.

I would definetely recommend this place
Studio is small, but comfortable and it has all you need. Plus it s really clean, quiet and the location is great ( walking distance to everywhere ).

The staff is extremelly nice, polite and welcoming.

A fabulous experience, i will come again!!

Excellent location. Near metro and near many restaurants and nightlife. Quiet hotel near many things. Room is nice but stairs to get to room are narrow and steep. Clean attractive room at a great size.

Really enjoyed our stay.Small rooms but brilliantly organised. Bed was lovely, breakfast good, it was clean and the staff were really helpful. Was handy to 2 metro stations, restaurants, bars and shops. Would stay again.

We hardly slept for 3 nights due to the noise of speeding motorbikes right out of our window. We ran away from this place even though we booked 4 more nights. The room felt like a cage with ~2 meters of height (even less in the bathroom). I slept with my feet in the air as the bed was too short for a person 1.9 meters tall. The mattress was very hard as well. Very steep and narrow stairs leading to the room. Arrogant and impolite staff. No refund whatsoever for the ruined vacations.

From the start the staff were very helpful. The room immaculate! We functioning kitchen. The bathroom was tiny though! Shower was a decent size however if you we bigger than a UK 10 you were not fitting in there. Good price.
The area was great, 3 metro all in walking distance. All metro can take you to the same places, just jump off at the stop with connecting number. Paris is a beautiful city. I went with my daughter for her 21st & had an amazing experience xx

I chose Hotel de l'Horloge because I wanted to self cater and to live in Parisian style. This was a great choice and it ticked all my boxes. Self catering, comfortable bed, superb shower, easy access to Metro and daily shopping - think Boulangeries and Fromageries. I asked for a room change as the steps to my first room were a bit steep for me to manage and this was done with no fuss and I was delighted with my new room with a view of the roof garden opposite. The housekeeping was impeccable and nothing was too much trouble. A great choice and I would return here if there is another Paris opportunity.

The Hotel de l'Horloge is quiet, clean, great character and secure. The service was very quick, helpful and polite. It is located in a great area with lots of bars, restaurants and public transport close by.

Good hotel with a secure gate. It was a convenient stay just about half a kilometer from the ESCP where we were undergoing a business program for a week. Very near the metro MenilMontant as well as rue st. Maur across ESCP. There's no elevator in the hotel so you need to carry the bags up a very narrow flight of stairs. No AC in the room, so it was very stuffy in September. Thankfully the hotel staff were good enough to arrange for a fan. The room was small with a small electric cooking range and microwave. Utensils were provided. Very small bathroom, housekeeping was OK, so cleaning was done everyday. The hotel is located in a very narrow street so u might tend to miss it while coming. Lots of eating joints within walking distance. The hotel also serves breakfast if you give them a days advance notice.

I stayed 11 times in Hotel de l'Horloge so far, always when I was in Paris for training, and would definitely recommend it! The studios are spacious, clean, in good condition and have everything you need. The building is on a quiet street in a trendy, local and safe neighborhood. It's also a great place to stay if you are in Paris for a longer period of time. The only thing I would criticize is that the wifi was sometimes a bit slow. But overall, very good stay and I would love to go back. Last but not least, everyone at Hotel de l'Horloge was very friendly and made you feel really welcome.

Very warm, friendly and helpful staff. Very clean rooms and extremely clean towels and bedding. I have been to many hotels in France (sometimes 4 star) and this hotel has the cleanest towels and bedding of them all.

This hotel is also very close to the Metro, groceries, pharmacies etc. The internet has been problematic but they are doing there best to find a solution for it.

I would give them 10 stars out of 5 if I could. Bravo! :)

My wife and I stayed here from Sept 21-Oct 10. You won't be disappointed if booking this property. It was very convenient to the Metro (Menilmontant, #2, Blue Line). Step off the Metro and it's five minutes to your room. Bus #96 stops five minutes away...takes you to the center of the tourist area (St. Michel/Notre Dame). Hotel de l'Horloge is surrounded by small restaurants/cafes, nice bakery near by, laundry place right around the corner. Want American style "fast food" for a change...McDonalds, KFC, and Subway are a short five minute walk. This place has it all! Oh...and the rooms are great too...clean, clean, clean...our room had a nice stove, micro, frig, dishes, utensils, etc... Place is also safe (entry is limited to key holders) When we go back to Paris we'll stay here.

The place in the city quite good (you could reach metro station, shop, caffe, bar in a few minutes) The service of room was perfect! Breakfast in the morning to your room it's fantastic:)

Hope to back soon:)

Best Regards!

Andrius

A good-sized room (we were in a double studio), with bright, modern decor. Everything was spotlessly clean. A comfortable bed and a reasonable amount of storage for clothes. The bathroom was small, but there were plenty of shelves and cupboard space, as well as a useful selection of toiletries. The staff were friendly, welcoming and helpful. Most of the rooms are set back from this side street, so we found it very quiet.

I booked two rooms - one for me and one for my son. They were close together which was great. I felt very safe as the complex is gated. The location was close to the metro and a taxi stand, so getting around was easy! Everything was provided in the apartment in a very compact form (except a hair-dryer). The staff was very friendly and helpful, and seemed to be there all the time! The bakery on the corner was really convenient and cheap!

The room was clean and cozy with a small kitchenette that I loved. There was enough dishes to use for 2 people. However, the bathroom was too small for my boyfriend and he had trouble fitting in! The staff were friendly and nice. One of them could speak English which was great! The neighborhood looks a bit rough but we had no problem. The subway/metro station is very close to the hotel and very convenient. The WiFi was awful. Attached you can find the photos of the room the moment we checked in. Overall I'm happy with my stay in this hotel.

This hotel is in a great location, just 1 minute from the metro. We travelled all over Paris, it was easy using the metro. The staff was great and the rooms were cleaned every day. We depend strongly on the internet and the wifi connection was great, just remember each connection needs a seperate password. Don't worry its free, just ask the desk. The prices on the rooms vary, depends on your needs but they have great prices. First check with hotels.com and other networks. Will stay there again. Great value.

I wish I'd chosen this guesthouse-style courtyard hotel in a quiet neighborhood near Pere Lachaise for my entire stay in Paris. From the courtesy of the staff to the amenities, including a well-appointed kitchenette, the room was absolutely perfect. Thank you hotel de l'Horloge! Highly recommended!

This was a great surprise for the price. Everything is new, modern and clean. The staff has been very helpful.
The location is good, very close to the metro.
I would recommend it as it is not easy to find good hotels at an affordable price in Paris

Already before we left, the staff at the hotel was very helpful to answer any practical questions I had, from getting to Disneyland to which metro ticket it was smart to buy. We had a studio(appartement) with everything we needed to make food. They don`t serve breakfast, but not far to shops, and there is a great boulangerie at the corner close by, where you can buy fresh, almost right out the oven, baguettes and delicous cakes. There are many restaurants close by, from McDonalds to pizzas to f. ex Marrocan couscous. We were two adults and two teenagers and the room was big, comfy, clean, new and modern. Daily cleaning. You get a lot for the price!
It was unusally hot in Paris when we were there, there is no airconditioning but there was a fan there so it served the purpose. A little bit of traffic noise during the night (on the side facing the street) but the hotel is in an alley which is very quiet, so no big problem.The hotel is a little bit outside the center of Paris, close to Bellville, but metrostations are close by and very efficient. Getting to Disneyland was very easy from here (it`s in the same direction). Safe neighborhood which comes to life in the evenings!
What stood out was the very helpful and welcoming englishspeaking staff. They helped us with every questions we had, and everything we needed, they really made our stay a great one!
Would recommend this hotel without hesitation!

The location was great for the things we wanted to do and the staff could not have been more helpful however, I did find the room very compact and the bathroom was tiny too although the shower is a good size. The room was spotless and cleaned daily. It was ok for a weekend visit but I would not have wanted to stay any longer. The area was ok in one direction but not okay in the other direction and once we knew this we felt more comfortable and found some nice restaurants...the flea market was more like a boot sale and you would have to search hard for an antique, but the proximity to the Pere Lechaise Cemetry is just what I wanted

I second the clean, comfortable, functional guests' opinions. ..., although, be a bit careful on the wooden stairs (not part of the remodel). My niece and I had a great stay; they provided her with a hair dryer, and me with a second Wi-Fi account, free of charge, no questions asked. Taxi?? It's walking distance from both the Me'nilmontant and Pe're Lachaise Metro stations, and the 69 bus line at Pe're Lachaise on Rue du Chemin Vert goes clear across town. It is not dangerous. It is a mixed ethnicity, working class neighborhood, with a bakery on the (Boulevard de Me'nilmontant) corner, and a live jazz group in the corner restaurant across from it. Excellent Greek food at Zagros nearby; Kurdish owner sat with us with complimentary Armagnacs. Special thanks to the Spanish hotel night clerk!

Went here for a 3 day break in Paris around my wifes birthday, and like trying different areas. This is just round the corner (walking distance) from Pre Lachaise, which is a fascinating cemetery to walk around.
The hotel is in a gated area off an alley, which connects to a main road that has a large market at the weekend. The hotel is sandwiched between 3 metro stations, giving you access to metro lines 2 & 3 and just round the corner from Rue Oberkamf, which is a great place to look for food, so it is a good place to base a wandering weekend. There is a bakery on the corner for the morning bread.

The room itself is very small, but has a double bed, table and chairs, TV, clocks, microwave, tea/coffee facilities and hotplates, as well as a tiny shower / sink in its own little room. It was pretty comfortable and surprisingly quiet for Paris. The staff were friendly but couldn't really speak English, which wasn't an issue as my wife speaks French, but would have been an issue with my French

I have been traveling Europe for two months and this is the worst hotel that I have stayed in. While the rooms were okay (bed, decent bathroom, etc), the location was awful (seemed to be dangerous and not a safe place to be at night) and we were forced to take a taxi everywhere. The worst part of the hotel was the staff. They were not accommodating, extremely rude, and just seemed to want to take our money and not hear from us again.

Our room was clean, comfortable and the kitchen well equipped. It is situated near Menilmontant and not as centrally as displayed on the map on Tripadvisor! There are some great reasonably priced couscous restaurants nearby and a bakery for breakfast at the end of the road. A good base from which to explore Paris. Would stay again.

I just needed a reasonably priced hotel for a 2-day visit to Paris. My room in Hotel de l'Horloge was small but comfortable. Even included a kitchenette which I didn't really need. Also close to Metro, so suited me very well. Main reason for this review is that the manager-on-duty was super helpful. The hotel is situated in a gated side street, so is quiet (unusual in Paris) and secure.
